---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'March 2, 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — Matrix Digital Media"
  description="Privacy policy for all apps published by Matrix Digital Media LLC."
>
  <Header />

  <main class="policy-page">
    <div class="container">

      <div class="policy-header">
        <a href="/" class="back-link">← Home</a>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="meta">Matrix Digital Media LLC &mdash; Last updated {lastUpdated}</p>
      </div>

      <div class="policy-body">

        <p class="intro">
          This Privacy Policy applies to all mobile applications and digital products published
          by <strong>Matrix Digital Media LLC</strong> ("we," "us," or "our"), including HiveHelper
          and any future apps. By using our apps, you agree to the practices described below.
        </p>

        <section>
          <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

          <h3>Information You Provide</h3>
          <p>
            Our apps allow you to enter and store content such as logs, notes, observations, and
            other data you create within the app. This information is stored locally on your device
            by default.
          </p>

          <h3>Data Submitted to AI Features</h3>
          <p>
            Certain features in our apps use third-party AI services to generate personalized
            guidance or analysis. When you use these features, relevant data you have entered —
            such as notes, observations, or other app content — may be transmitted to a
            third-party AI language model service provider to generate a response. This
            transmission occurs only when you actively use the feature. The data sent is used
            solely to generate your result and is subject to the AI provider's data handling
            practices.
          </p>
          <p>
            You are not required to use AI features. If you prefer not to transmit your data to
            an AI service, simply do not use those features.
          </p>

          <h3>Photos</h3>
          <p>
            If you attach photos within our apps, those photos are stored locally on your device
            by default. In certain features, photos may be submitted to a third-party AI image
            analysis service provider for automated processing. This only occurs when you
            explicitly use that feature and is subject to the provider's data handling practices.
          </p>

          <h3>Usage and Analytics Data</h3>
          <p>
            We collect anonymous usage data to understand how our apps are used and to improve
            the experience. This includes information such as which features are used, how often,
            and general interaction patterns. This data does not include the content of your
            personal entries and is not linked to your identity.
          </p>
          <p>
            Analytics are powered by <strong>Firebase Analytics</strong> (Google LLC). For more
            information on how Firebase handles data, visit
            <a href="https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              firebase.google.com/support/privacy
            </a>.
          </p>

          <h3>Purchase Information</h3>
          <p>
            If you make an in-app purchase, the transaction is processed entirely by Apple through
            the App Store. We receive confirmation of your purchase status (e.g., active
            subscription) but do not receive your payment details, credit card information, or
            billing address.
          </p>

          <h3>Device Information</h3>
          <p>
            We may collect general device information such as operating system version and device
            type for the purpose of crash reporting and compatibility improvements.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>To provide and maintain app functionality</li>
            <li>To generate AI-powered guidance or analysis when you request it</li>
            <li>To understand usage patterns and improve our products</li>
            <li>To verify purchase and subscription status</li>
            <li>To diagnose crashes and technical issues</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We do not sell your information to third parties. We do not use your data for
            targeted advertising.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>3. Data Storage and Transmission</h2>
          <p>
            All personal data you enter into our apps is stored locally on your device by default.
            We do not operate our own servers that receive or store your personal entries.
          </p>
          <p>
            Certain optional features — such as AI guidance — transmit relevant app content to
            third-party service providers to fulfill the request. These transmissions are described
            in Section 1 above and in Section 4 below. They occur only when you actively use
            the feature and are not stored by us.
          </p>
          <p>
            In future versions of our apps, we may offer optional cloud backup or sync features.
            If and when such features are introduced, they will be opt-in, clearly disclosed,
            and this policy will be updated accordingly.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>4. Third-Party Service Providers</h2>
          <p>
            Our apps may integrate with third-party service providers in the following categories.
            We select providers whose data practices are appropriate for the data being processed.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>App Store payment processing</strong> — In-app purchases and subscriptions
              are processed by Apple. Subject to
              <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Apple's Privacy Policy</a>.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Analytics</strong> — Anonymous usage analytics are collected via
              Firebase Analytics (Google LLC). Subject to
              <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>AI language model services</strong> — When you use an AI guidance feature,
              relevant app content (such as notes and observations you have entered) is transmitted
              to a third-party AI language model provider to generate your result.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>AI image analysis services</strong> — When you use a photo analysis feature,
              selected photos are transmitted to a third-party AI image analysis provider for
              processing.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We may update or change our service providers over time. This policy describes the
            categories of services we use; specific providers may change without prior notice
            as long as data handling practices remain consistent with this policy.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>5. International Data Transfers</h2>
          <p>
            We are based in the United States. Some of our third-party service providers,
            including analytics and AI service providers, may process data outside of your
            country of residence, including in the United States. By using our apps, you
            acknowledge that your data may be transferred to and processed in countries
            that may have different data protection laws than your own.
          </p>
          <p>
            Where required, our service providers implement appropriate safeguards for
            international data transfers, such as standard contractual clauses approved
            by applicable regulatory authorities.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>6. User Accounts</h2>
          <p>
            Our current apps do not require you to create an account or provide personally
            identifying information such as your name or email address to use core features.
            Future versions may offer optional account creation to enable features such as
            cloud sync across devices.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>7. Data Retention and Deletion</h2>
          <p>
            All locally stored data remains on your device until you delete it within the app
            or uninstall the app. Uninstalling the app removes all locally stored data
            associated with it. Anonymous analytics data is retained per Firebase's standard
            retention policies.
          </p>
          <p>
            Data transmitted to AI service providers for feature fulfillment is not stored
            by us. Retention practices for that data are governed by the respective provider's
            policies.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            Our apps are not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly
            collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe a child has
            provided information through one of our apps, please contact us and we will take
            steps to address it.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>9. Your Rights</h2>
          <p>
            Because most data in our apps is stored locally on your device, you retain direct
            control over it at all times. You can delete your data within the app or by
            uninstalling the app.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you are located in the European Economic Area (EEA), United Kingdom, or another
            jurisdiction with applicable data protection rights, you may have the right to access,
            correct, or request deletion of personal data we or our service providers hold about
            you. To exercise these rights or ask questions about data processing, contact us at
            the address below.
          </p>
          <p>
            We do not use your data for targeted advertising or sell your data to third parties.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will update the
            "Last updated" date at the top of this page. We encourage you to review this policy
            periodically. Continued use of our apps after changes are posted constitutes
            acceptance of the updated policy.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
          <p>
            If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:<br />
            <a href="mailto:support@matrixnj.com">support@matrixnj.com</a>
          </p>
          <p>
            Matrix Digital Media LLC<br />
            New Jersey, United States
          </p>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .policy-page {
    padding-top: calc(var(--header-h) + 4rem);
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .policy-header {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .back-link:hover { color: var(--text); }

  .policy-header h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .meta {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .policy-body {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .intro {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  section:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  ul {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.75rem 1.25rem;
  }

  ul li {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--accent-1);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  a:hover { opacity: 0.8; }

  strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 600; }
</style>
